HEADWORD: Zygophyllaceae
<hw>Zy`go*phyl*la"ce*ae</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A
natural family of small trees, shrubs, and herbs of warm arid and saline
regions; it is often resinous, and some are poisonous. It contains the
genera <gen>Zygophyllum</gen>; <gen>Tribulus</gen>; <gen>Guaiacum;</gen>
and <gen>Larrea</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> family <fam>Zygophyllaceae</fam>, bean-caper
family.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zygophyllum</ent>⟦br⟧
